The paper deals with image processing and computer vision techniques for visible watermark removal, which falls under the scope of computer vision (cs.CV) and multimedia (cs.MM). The paper also discusses the use of generative adversarial networks (GANs) for image-to-image translation, which is a popular topic in computer graphics (cs.GR). The paper also addresses the issue of copyright protection, which is related to cryptography (cs.CR) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
